<p style="text-align:justify;">they attribute all the blessings of life.  Their Idols are either Stones or trunks of trees rudely carved.  They believe in a good and an evil principle, which they suppose to be at continual variance &#8211; the women are excluded from worship.  They pay great reverence to the manes of the dead, and dread them extremely &#8211; they prognosticate events and draw figures on drums for that purpose.  The flesh of Rein-Deer which they dry in the cold they pound into powder with the inner rind of the pine tree, and which they substitute for bread.  They make broth of fish and flesh together &#8211; their usual drink is water heated in a kettle, which in winter hangs continually on the fire.  The conquest of a bear is the most honourable exploit they can perform; and such heroes as have been triumphant in those wars,</p>

